subSubSection.paragraph:
TERMINALIA. Body of penis elongate (W:L ratio: 0.34), almost 2 × shorter than apodemes, sides subparallel in dorsal view, narrowing in apical 1/5, apex obtuse; in lateral view curvature stronger in basal half, moderate in apical half, width regular (
Fig. 6D
).

As is the case in several species of Derelomini (
Haran et al. 2020
), this species has major and minor males. In minor males, the prosternal process may be reduced to a small tubercle between the procoxae. This species represents the first case of a prosternal process oriented backward in derelomine weevils.
